* orgmode-daedalus

  A parser and pretty-printer for the Org-Mode (https://orgmode.org) document
  format.

  - Parsing is implemented using the
    Galois Daedalus (https://github.com/GaloisInc/daedalus) parser (which
    permits generation of C, C++, and Rust parsers as well).

    + Parsing errors are reported via
      the diagnose (https://hackage.haskell.org/package/diagnose) package.

  - Pretty-printing is implemented using
    the sayable (https://hackage.haskell.org/package/sayable) package.

  Development and usage is supported by
  the eng (https://github.com/GaloisInc/eng) tool. Install this tool and
  type `eng' in this directory for more information.



* OrgMode support details

  Note that structural and markup parsing are distinct operations: markup is
  parsed entirely within each individual structural element.

